description.narrative: The Government of Indonesia;planned, implemented and monitored COVID-19 interventions for children and their families by applying data and innovation. Facebook and satellite imagery data supported poverty projection and assessment of preparedness of schools and health facilities. The One Data Vaccination System improved monitoring of COVID-19 responses, while the digitized COVID-19 Vaccine Introduction tool supported real-time monitoring, and the RapidPro-based monitoring platform complemented the Government’s existing system. The piloting of the Early Childhood Development Index;secured the Government’s commitment for;planning, implementation, monitoring and reporting on the SDGs; and the partnership with the think-tank supported evidence generation and advocacy for children. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:02/02/2022
